'''Nico O'Reilly''' (born 21 March 2005) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] or [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|ManchesC}} club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and the [[England national football team|England national team]].

A product of Manchester City's [[Manchester City F.C. Under-21s and Academy|academy]], O'Reilly made his senior debut in 2024. He won his first major trophy with the club in his second season, scoring a brace in the [[2026 EFL Cup final]].

A [[England national youth football team|youth international]] for England, O'Reilly made his senior debut in 2025.

==Early life==
Nico O'Reilly<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/4030168 |title=Premier League clubs publish 2023/24 retained lists |publisher=Premier League |date=5 June 2024 |access-date=}}</ref> was born on 21 March 2005 in [[Manchester]].<ref name="ManCityProfile">{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/players/nico-oreilly |title=Nico O'Reilly |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |access-date=24 August 2024}}</ref> He was first spotted by Manchester City scouts at age six while playing football in the [[Moston, Manchester|Moston]] area of Manchester,<ref name="NY Times">{{Cite news |last=Taylor |first=Daniel |date=12 November 2025 |title=The making of Nico O'Reilly, as told by his mum and those who discovered him |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6795660/2025/11/11/nico-oreilly-making-of-manchester-city/ |access-date=20 April 2026 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> and he joined the [[Manchester City F.C. Under-21s and Academy|club’s academy]] two years later at age eight.<ref name="ManCityProfile"/> He was raised by his mother, Holli, on an estate on the border of [[Ancoats]] and [[Collyhurst]].<ref name="NY Times"/> He attended St Patrick's RC Primary School in Collyhurst, the same school that [[World Cup]] winner [[Nobby Stiles]] attended.<ref>{{Cite news |date=12 November 2025 |title=England Squad Guide |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/extra/fm77g492yy/england-2026-world-cup-squad-guide#section-Goalkeepers-BAifjJ0klI |access-date=22 May 2026 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> He is of [[Jamaica|Jamaican]] descent through his father.<ref>{{Cite news |date=12 November 2025 |title=Meet Holli O'Reilly: The Single Mother Who Raised Manchester City's Nico O'Reilly |url=https://www.bbntimes.com/society/meet-holli-o-reilly-the-single-mother-who-raised-manchester-city-s-nico-o-reilly|access-date=10 April 2026 |work=BBN Times |language=en-US|first=Felix|last=Yim}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Manchester City===
====Early career====
O'Reilly moved up to the Manchester City under-23 side towards the end of the 2021–22 season, and subsequently signed his first professional contract with the club in July 2022.<ref>{{cite news|first=Joe|last=Bray|date=8 July 2022|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-contract-news-academy-24432628|website=Manchester Evening News|title=Two Man City players sign contract extensions as 13 youngsters sign first professional deals}}</ref> O'Reilly captained the under-18s during the 2022–23 season.<ref>{{cite web|first=Paul|last=Vegas|url=https://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/man-city-u18-captain-nico-o-reilly-proud-of-brace-in-victory-over-man-utd-4454062|title= Man City U18 captain Nico O'Reilly proud of brace in victory over Man Utd|website=Tribal Football}}</ref> He made some headlines after he was filmed scoring an overhead [[scorpion kick]] in the 95th minute of an under-18s match for
Manchester City against Middlesbrough in April 2023.<ref>{{cite news|first=Matthew|last=Abbott|date=8 April 2023|access-date=24 May 2023|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-scorpion-nico-oreilly-26660242|website=Manchester Evening News|title='Puskas award incoming' – Man City fans rave about incredible Academy team wonder goal|archive-date=24 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230524202538/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-scorpion-nico-oreilly-26660242|url-status=live}}</ref> A week later, he scored with a forty-yard chip against Manchester United under-18s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://elitescholars.co.uk/2023/04/15/u18-premier-league-nico-oreilly-scores-brace-as-city-triumphs-over-united-in-u18-mini-derby/|first=Rob|last=Binns|accessdate=24 May 2023|title=FOOTBALLU18 Premier League: Nico O'Reilly scores brace as City triumphs over United in U18 mini-derby|date=31 May 2023|website=Elite Scholars|archive-date=24 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230524201506/https://elitescholars.co.uk/2023/04/15/u18-premier-league-nico-oreilly-scores-brace-as-city-triumphs-over-united-in-u18-mini-derby/|url-status=live}}</ref>

O'Reilly trained with the Manchester City first-team on a warm weather training camp to [[Abu Dhabi]] in December 2022.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/manchester-city-training-camp-squad-25681518|first=Joe|last=Bray|date=5 December 2022|website=Manchester Evening News|title=Manchester City training camp squad for trip to Abu Dhabi confirmed|archive-date=24 May 2023|access-date=24 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230524210844/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/manchester-city-training-camp-squad-25681518|url-status=live}}</ref> He was included in the match day squad for their [[Premier League]] fixture away to [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] on 24 May 2023, but remained on the substitutes' bench.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.manchesterworld.uk/sport/football/manchester-city/man-city-injury-grealish-laporte-dias-akanji-brighton-4156853|first=Michael|last=Plant|date=24 May 2023|title='Not fit' – Pep Guardiola gives update on wave of injuries in Man City camp|website=Manchester World|access-date=24 May 2023|archive-date=24 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230524192757/https://www.manchesterworld.uk/sport/football/manchester-city/man-city-injury-grealish-laporte-dias-akanji-brighton-4156853|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2023/05/24/england/premier-league/brighton--hove-albion-fc/manchester-city-football-club/3800291/|title=Brighton vs. Man City|date=24 May 2023|website=Soccerway|access-date=24 May 2023|archive-date=24 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230524192903/https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2023/05/24/england/premier-league/brighton--hove-albion-fc/manchester-city-football-club/3800291/|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2024–25 season====
O'Reilly made his senior debut in the [[2024 FA Community Shield]] against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on 10 August 2024.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cx2xqpzw47xo|date=12 August 2024|accessdate=13 August 2024|website=BBC Sport|title=Which youngster will emerge?|first=Simon|last=Stone|archive-date=13 August 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240813163215/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cx2xqpzw47xo|url-status=live}}</ref> On 11 January 2025, O'Reilly scored his first goal for Manchester City in an [[2024–25 FA Cup|FA Cup]] third round home match against [[EFL League Two|League Two]] side [[Salford City F.C.|Salford City]] which eventually ended in an 8–0 win.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Manchester City vs Salford City: FA Cup stats & head-to-head |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/crmngkjg221t |access-date=11 January 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=9 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250209152126/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/crmngkjg221t |url-status=live }}</ref> Two months later, on 1 March, he netted his first career brace in a 3–1 home win over [[EFL Championship|Championship]] side [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]] in the fifth round of the competition.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Manchester City vs Plymouth Argyle: FA Cup stats & head-to-head |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c3w1eg69v8pt |access-date=2 March 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=1 March 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250301193817/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c3w1eg69v8pt |url-status=live }}</ref> In the following quarter-final, on 30 March, he assisted both goals in a 2–1 away victory over [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]], playing a role in his team’s progression to the semi-finals and earning the Man of the Match award for his performance.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c07z3l1g2p4t |title=AFC Bournemouth 1–2 Manchester City |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |date=30 March 2025 |access-date=6 April 2025 |archive-date=6 April 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250406143846/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c07z3l1g2p4t |url-status=live }}</ref> On 2 April, O'Reilly made his first Premier League start for City in a 2–0 home win against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]], playing the full 90 minutes.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/704574/leicester-city-manchester-city |title=Man City 2–0 Leicester City (Apr 2, 2025) Final Score |access-date=3 April 2025 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> On 12 April, O'Reilly scored his first goal in the Premier League in a 5–2 City victory at home against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Stone |first=Simon |title=Manchester City 5–2 Crystal Palace |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cgjl5ye9ylnt |website=BBC Sport |date=12 April 2025 |access-date=19 April 2025 |archive-date=14 April 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250414000157/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cgjl5ye9ylnt |url-status=live }}</ref>

====2025–26 season====
On 26 September 2025, O'Reilly signed a new five-year contract with Manchester City, keeping him at the club until the summer of 2030.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/nico-oreilly-signs-new-contract-manchester-city-63894493 |title=O'Reilly signs fresh City contract! |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=26 September 2025 |access-date=26 September 2025}}</ref> O'Reilly scored his first [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] goal in a 2–1 victory over [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] on 10 December 2025.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Kallas |first=Fernando |date=10 December 2025 |title=Manchester City rally to beat Real Madrid 2–1 at Bernabeu |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/manchester-city-rally-beat-real-madrid-2-1-bernabeu-2025-12-10/ |access-date=21 February 2026 |work=[[Reuters]]}}</ref> On 21 February 2026, O'Reilly scored his first league brace to secure a 2–1 victory over [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] and cut [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]'s lead in the league to just two points.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Hampson |first=Andy |date=21 February 2026 |title=Man City cut Arsenal's Premier League lead to two points after Newcastle victory |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league-newcastle-arsenal-mikel-arteta-city-b2925097.html |access-date=21 February 2026 |work=[[The Independent]]}}</ref> A month later, on 22 March, the day after he turned 21, O'Reilly scored a brace in a 2–0 victory against Arsenal in the [[2026 EFL Cup final|EFL Cup final]], securing his club's ninth title in the competition.<ref>{{cite web |last=Furniss |first=Matt |url=https://theanalyst.com/articles/arsenal-vs-manchester-city-stats-opta-league-cup-final-2026 |title=Arsenal 0–2 Manchester City Stats: O'Reilly Double Gives Guardiola Record-Breaking Fifth League Cup Title |publisher=Opta Analyst |date=22 March 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
O'Reilly scored his first goal for the [[England national under-16 football team|England under-16s]] against [[Northern Ireland national under-16 football team|Northern Ireland]] on 3 June 2021, in a 6–0 win.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2021/06/03/world/under-16-friendlies/england-u16/northern-ireland-u16/3511107/|website=Soccerway|title=England U16 vs. Northern Ireland U16|date=3 June 2021|access-date=24 May 2023|archive-date=24 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230524194423/https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2021/06/03/world/under-16-friendlies/england-u16/northern-ireland-u16/3511107/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Peter|last=Smith|website=Stoke Sentinel|date=3 June 2021|accessdate=24 May 2023|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2021/06/03/world/under-16-friendlies/england-u16/northern-ireland-u16/3511107/|title=Stoke City youth striker bangs in hat-trick on England duty|archive-date=24 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230524194423/https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2021/06/03/world/under-16-friendlies/england-u16/northern-ireland-u16/3511107/|url-status=live}}</ref> A few months later, he scored his first goal for the [[England national under-17 football team|England U17]] side, in the 88th minute of a 2–2 draw away against [[Slovakia national under-17 football team|Slovakia]] on 21 October 2022.<ref>{{cite web|first=Frank|last=Smith|url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2021/Oct/22/England-under-17s-Slovakia-report-20211022|title=Slovakia 2–2 England|date=21 October 2022|access-date=24 May 2023|archive-date=28 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230328180844/https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2021/Oct/22/England-under-17s-Slovakia-report-20211022|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 6 September 2024, O'Reilly made his [[England national under-20 football team|England U20]] debut during a 1–1 draw away to [[Turkey national under-20 football team|Turkey]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Drury |first=Adam |url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2024/Sep/06/england-mens-elite-league-squad-turkiye-match-report-20240609 |title=Report: England Elite League Squad 1–1 Turkiye |publisher=The Football Association |date=6 September 2024 |access-date=27 September 2024}}</ref> On 29 August 2025, O'Reilly was called up to the [[England national under-21 football team|under-21s]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Veevers |first=Nicholas |url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2025/Aug/29/england-mens-under-21s-squad-announced-for-kazakhstan-game-in-september-20252908 |title=England MU21s squad named for Kazakhstan trip |publisher=The Football Association |date=29 August 2025 |access-date=6 October 2025}}</ref>

On 6 October 2025, O'Reilly received his first call-up to the [[England national football team|England senior team]] after [[Reece James]] withdrew from the squad with injury.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2025/Oct/06/england-mens-squad-updates-october-international-camp-20250610?q=nico%20o%27reilly |title=England squad update: Nico O'Reilly joins men's squad |publisher=The Football Association |date=6 October 2025 |access-date=6 October 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/nico-oreilly-england-call-up-63895342 |title=O'Reilly handed maiden senior England call-up |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=6 October 2025 |access-date=6 October 2025}}</ref> He was an unused substitute in England's 3–0 friendly win over [[Wales national football team|Wales]] at [[Wembley Stadium]] on 9 October.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cvg9j7lqvqvt#Line-ups|title=England 3–0 Wales|date=9 October 2025|access-date=12 October 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

He made his England senior team debut during a 2–0 win over [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]] at Wembley Stadium.<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 November 2025|title=Nico's night, Bellingham's bench: England XI to face Serbia |url=https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/england/world-cup-2026/news/nicos-night-bellinghams-bench-england-xi-to-face-serbia-confirmed_585689.html |access-date=15 November 2025|website=Sports Mole}}</ref>

==Style of play==
O'Reilly has been described as an attacking midfielder with "flair" who is "graceful and fluid with the ball at his feet".<ref>{{cite web|website=The Times|url=https://www.thetimes.com/sport/football/article/if-gareth-southgate-saw-arsenal-and-manchester-city-youth-teams-maybe-he-wouldn-t-worry-as-much-6w6zzjtng|access-date=24 May 2023|title= Gareth Southgate wouldn't be worried if he watched Arsenal and Manchester City youth|first=Hamzah|last=Khalique-Loonat|date=5 April 2023}}</ref>  O'Reilly has also been described as "Positionless" when starting at left-back due to his ability to carry the ball, push high up, and quickly transition between attack and defense thanks to his physicality and "completeness".<ref>{{Cite web |title='He is so complete' - Pep Guardiola in awe of Man City star Nico O'Reilly after Newcastle brace |url=https://www.foxsports.com/articles/soccer/he-is-so-complete-pep-guardiola-in-awe-of-man-city-star-nico-oreilly-after-newcastle-brace |access-date=25 April 2026 |website=www.foxsports.com |language=en-US}}</ref>

